myfile.html - means same folder
../myfile.html - Means Up one level
/myfile.html - means root folder
http://myserver.com/myfile.html - absolute adressing

# CSS Notes

selector{} - means which element you want to access
for example: p {} - accesses p element, applies to everysingle p tag.

## nested tags
nav a {} - accesses a tags under nav sections.
nav ul li {} - accesses ul li under nav sections.

##by class
.button{} acceses button class

##by id
#bios {} accesses element with id "bios" 

##css priority
1. id
2. class
3. nested tags
4. tags

##tips for css
-- be as specific as possible
-- use id ands class if not sure
-- two fonts and two colours are usually enough. don't go crazy.

-- font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif (use Helvetica first, if not available, use the rest)
-- google fonts give a good resource!
-- you can use inspect and click on element to play with css effects.